<subSubSection id="6EF16510FF81FFABF7C024BBFE55FB8E" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="255" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2654369BFF81FFACF7C024BBFED7F8A5" blockId="3.[174,1233,1625,1844]" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">
<emphasis id="149FEA89FF81FFACF7C024BBFEA3F922" bold="true" box="[227,356,1689,1715]" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Posterior notopleural seta white, anepisternal and katepisternal setae black; femora at mostly black (
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF81FFACF6E0249BFDC9F945" box="[451,526,1721,1748]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,937,959]" captionTargetBox="[331,1069,174,931]" captionTargetId="figure-314@4.[316,1089,171,940]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 17–20. C. loewiana. 17 — ♀, habitus, right; 18 — mesonotum, dorsally; 19 — wing (SIZK); 20 — abdomen (SMNC)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452432" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452432/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">fig. 17</figureCitation>
); wing pattern with 2 hyaline spots in cell br; apex of r 
<subScript id="BA6F34DEFF81FFACF35F24EEFB51F94B" attach="left" box="[1148,1174,1740,1754]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">2+3</subScript>
with 2 isolated spots, base of cell r 
<subScript id="BA6F34DEFF81FFACF6DC24CEFDDEF96B" attach="left" box="[511,537,1772,1786]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">4+5</subScript>
with one oval spot (
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF81FFACF42624FBFC97F965" box="[773,848,1753,1780]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,937,959]" captionTargetBox="[331,1069,174,931]" captionTargetId="figure-314@4.[316,1089,171,940]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 17–20. C. loewiana. 17 — ♀, habitus, right; 18 — mesonotum, dorsally; 19 — wing (SIZK); 20 — abdomen (SMNC)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452432" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452432/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">fig. 19</figureCitation>
); frons fine trichose. Oviscape as long as 2 preceding abdominal tergites; length of aculeus about 4.2 times as long as wide (
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF81FFACF795253BFEC4F8A5" box="[182,259,1817,1844]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,937,959]" captionTargetBox="[331,1069,174,931]" captionTargetId="figure-314@4.[316,1089,171,940]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 17–20. C. loewiana. 17 — ♀, habitus, right; 18 — mesonotum, dorsally; 19 — wing (SIZK); 20 — abdomen (SMNC)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452432" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452432/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">fig. 20</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="72946613FF86FFABF785218BFEC7FC4B" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452432" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6452432" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452432/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" startId="4.[166,199,937,959]" targetBox="[331,1069,174,931]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="2654369BFF86FFABF785218BFEC7FC4B" blockId="4.[166,1225,936,986]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">
