<subSubSection id="6EF16510FF86FFABF7FD261AFC67FBE2" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2654369BFF86FFABF7FD261AFC67FBE2" blockId="4.[169,1227,1080,1139]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">
<emphasis id="149FEA89FF86FFABF7FD261AFEAAFBC3" bold="true" box="[222,365,1080,1106]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Comments.</emphasis>
This species occurs locally in the Palaearctic 
<collectingRegion id="E42FF879FF86FFABF454261AFC09FBC3" box="[887,974,1080,1106]" country="Iraq" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Region</collectingRegion>
. Larvae feed in flower heads of 
<taxonomicName id="E1EB4D18FF86FFABF632267AFE2EFBE3" box="[273,489,1112,1138]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Solidago" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="virgaurea">
<emphasis id="149FEA89FF86FFABF632267AFE2EFBE3" box="[273,489,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Solidago virgaurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. and 
<taxonomicName id="E1EB4D18FF86FFABF563267BFD1AFBE3" box="[576,733,1112,1139]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Aster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amellus">
<emphasis id="149FEA89FF86FFABF563267BFD1AFBE3" box="[576,733,1112,1139]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Aster amellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<bibRefCitation id="427A4B6AFF86FFABF42A267BFC54FBE2" author="Merz B." box="[777,915,1112,1139]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" refId="ref4891" refString="Merz B. Diptera: Tephritidae / Insecta Helvetica Fauna. - Geneve: Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 1994. - 10. - 198 S." type="book" year="1994">Merz, 1994</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
